ociety',523,'2014-10-29 05:01:35',1),('photo','post_page_378004348924081','Spinach with Chickpeas and Fried Eggs    Ingredients:        3 tablespoons olive oil_ divided_ plus more      4 medium garlic cloves_ thinly sliced_ divided      8 cups spinach_ coarsely chopped      Kosher salt_ freshly ground pepper      1 cup chopped onion      1 teaspoon cumin seeds      1/4 teaspoon smoked paprika      2 15-ounce cans chickpeas_ rinsed      5 canned whole tomatoes_ crushed      3 cups (or more) vegetable broth      4 large eggs      Preparations:   Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a large heavy pot over medium heat. When oil begins to shimmer_ add 1 garlic clove. Stir until beginning to turn golden brown_ 1-2 minutes. Add spinach to pot. Toss to coat; season with salt and pepper. Cook until spinach is wilted but still bright green_ 2-3 minutes. Transfer to a medium bowl; set aside. Wipe out pot.    Heat 2 tablespoons oil in same pot over medium heat. When oil begins to shimmer_ add onion and 3 garlic cloves. Cook_ stirring often_ until onion is softened_ 3-4 minutes.    Add cumin and paprika; stir until cumin is toasted and fragrant_ 1-2 minutes. Add chickpeas and tomatoes; stir to coat. Cook until tomatoes start to caramelize and chickpeas begin to brown_ 8-10 minutes. Add 3 cups broth; bring to a simmer_ scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan. Reduce heat to medium; simmer_ occasionally mashing some chickpeas with the back of a spoon or a potato masher_ until sauce is thickened_ 15-20 minutes. Fold in spinach; simmer for flavors to meld_ adding more broth by 1/4-cupfuls if too thick_ 8Ã±10 minutes.    Pour oil into a large heavy skillet to a depth of 1/8_ (about 1/4 cup). Heat until oil begins to shimmer. Crack 2 eggs into hot oil_ spacing apart. Using a large spoon_ carefully baste whites (not yolks) with oil until whites are set and edges are crunchy_ lacy_ and golden brown_ 2-3 minutes (do not turn). Season eggs with salt and pepper. Transfer to a plate and repeat with remaining 2 eggs.    Spoon chickpea stew into bowls and top each with a fried egg.','https://fbcdn-sphotos-c-a.akamaihd.net/hphotos-ak-xpa1/v/t1.0-9/s130x130/61157_434400176617831_1677454507_n.jpg?oh=3785d092d1fdfda84577ba2bc07a1be3&oe=54ECBFB7&__gda__=1425498570_0640e26477e59c831ba484a8cf547a1b','https://www.facebook.com/365cps/photos/a.380809678643548.87582.378004348924081/434400176617831/?type=1&relevant_count=1','facebook.com','2012-11-01T01:56:21+0000',1351734981,2,3,0,0,0,0,0,2,'378004348924081_434400206617828','https://www.facebook.com/378004348924081/posts/434400206617828','365 Cancer Prevention Society',524,'2014-10-29 05:01:35',1),('photo','post_page_378004348924081','SLOW ROASTED  TOMATOES    Ingredients:  4 pounds plum tomatoes_ halved lengthwise  6 garlic cloves_ minced  5 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil    Preparations:   Preheat oven to 200Â°F with racks in upper and lower thirds.    Put tomatoes_ cut side up_ in 2 large 4-sided sheet pans. Combine garlic and oil and spoon over tomatoes. Season tomatoes with salt and pepper and roast in oven 6 to 8 hours (tomatoes will be greatly reduced in size but still moist). Cool.','https://fbcdn-sphotos-d-a.akamaihd.net/hphotos-ak-prn2/v/t1.0-9/s130x130/14156_434399133284602_1418004142_n.jpg?oh=a58f0e840cdd54b1b200431ee3d6d427&oe=54F03E6F&__gda__=1420780318_539c385774601982cc98fdba2c2984f8','https://www.facebook.com/365cps/photos/a.380809678643548.87582.378004348924081/434399133284602/?type=1&relevant_count=1','facebook.com','2012-11-01T01:52:02+0000',1351734722,2,2,0,0,0,0,0,2,'378004348924081_434399143284601','https://www.facebook.com/378004348924081/posts/434399143284601','365 Cancer Prevention Society',525,'2014-10-29 05:01:35',1),('photo','post_page_378004348924081','Tomatoes for anyone who are concerned about prostate health_ cancer prevention_ fighting heart disease_ and weight loss!','https://fbcdn-sphotos-c-a.akamaihd.net/hphotos-ak-xaf1/v/t1.0-9/s130x130/10494_434398203284695_1166513966_n.jpg?oh=da35ae227dde6061bf66206c1101a2ac&oe=54ED8E6E&__gda__=1425357873_34bdb9b10734107a0a91ea6ffe696822','https://www.facebook.com/365cps/photos/a.380809678643548.87582.378004348924081/434398203284695/?type=1&relevant_count=1','facebook.com','2012-11-01T01:48:13+0000',1351734493,2,2,0,0,0,0,0,2,'378004348924081_434398226618026','https://www.facebook.com/378004348924081/posts/434398226618026','365 Cancer Prevention Society',526,'2014-10-29 05:01:35',1),('photo','post_page_378004348924081','Tomato Fish with Onion Recipe       Number of serving: 2    Preparing time: 10 minutes    Cooking time: 18 minutes      Ingredients:  250g firm fish fillet  Â½ onion_ chopped  2 tomatoes_ cut into pieces    Marinade Ingredients:  2 pinch salt    Seasoning Ingredients:  Â½ teaspoon cornflour  1 tablespoon tomato sauce  Â½ teaspoon sugar  4 tablespoons water    Method:  Mix fish fillet with marinade ingredients and let marinate for at least 10 minutes. Sprinkle cornflour to the fish. Heat up a wok under medium heat_ put in fish and fry for 5 minutes or until light brown. Remove fish. Heat Â½ tablespoon of oil under medium heat_ put in onion and stir fry for 2 minutes until fragrant. Put in tomatoes and continue to stir fry. Add seasoning ingredients and bring to the boil. Put in the fried fish and continue to cook for 1 minute. Remove and ready to serve.    Health tips:  Fishes like cod_ salmon_ white cod and flatfish contain a lot of Omega 3 which is good for the health. For people who have high blood cholesterol level and overweight_ the fish should be steamed instead of frying. Tomato is rich of lycopene_ an powerful antioxidant that believe to be able to prevent cancer.','https://scontent-b.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xpf1/v/t1.0-9/s130x130/12765_434040263320489_1183672240_n.jpg?oh=03aadfbef202e3d41dded33be58632b9&oe=54AB1B13','https://www.facebook.com/365cps/photos/a.380809678643548.87582.378004348924081/434040263320489/?type=1&relevant_count=1','facebook.com','2012-10-31T04:01:41+0000',1351656101,1,1,0,0,0,0,0,1,'378004348924081_434040293320486','https://www.facebook.com/378004348924081/posts/434040293320486','365 Cancer Prevention Society',527,'2014-10-29 05:01:35',1),('photo','post_page_378004348924081','Steamed Egg Custard Shrimp with Green Tea Recipe     Number of serving: 2    Preparation time: 10 minutes    Cooking time: 15 minutes      Ingredients:  6 Shrimps_ shell and devein shrimps (keep part the tail shell on). Rinse and wipe dry with cloth.  3 Eggs (whisked)  Green Tea Leaves  1 Â½ cups Water    Seasoning Ingredient:  Â½ teaspoon Salt  1 teaspoon Chicken powder    Marinade Ingredient:  1 teaspoon Egg white  1/8 teaspoon Salt  Â¼ teaspoon Caltrop starch    Method:  Marinate shrimps with marinade ingredient for 15 minutes. Jiggle in warm oil and drain with paper towel. Bring water to boil. Put in Green Tea Leaves and leave them to infuse 10 minutes. Strain the tea and discard the leaves. Take 1 Â¼ cups of tea and add seasoning to it. Pour the warm tea into whisked eggs and stir continuously until well mixed. Skim off the bubbles. Transfer the egg mixture to a deep bowl. Steam under low heat for 10 minutes. Put shrimps on top. Steam for 5 minutes more. Ready to serve.    Cooking Tips :  The best Chinese Tea to be used in this ingredient is LongJing (Dragon Well). One type of Chinese Green tea. Always jiggle shrimps in warm oil first before steaming or they tend to give much water when steamed. The shrimp also taste cruncher in this way.    Health Tips:  Green tea contain high anti-oxidant rich in catechin polyphenols that inhibiting the growth of cancer cells and kills them without harming healthy cells. It could also lowering LDL cholesterol levels_ prevent heart attacks and stroke and have body slimming effect.','https://scontent-a.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xaf1/v/t1.0-9/s130x130/285787_434039816653867_1469827753_n.jpg?oh=e0c7732f44dfc39f35cf83bc606fb0ec&oe=54F8D661','https://www.facebook.com/365cps/photos/a.380809678643548.87582.378004348924081/434039816653867/?type=1&relevant_count=1','facebook.com','2012-10-31T03:59:34+0000',1351655974,1,1,0,0,0,0,0,1,'378004348924081_434039833320532','https://www.facebook.com/378004348924081/posts/434039833320532','365 Cancer Prevention Society',528,'2014-10-29 05:01:35',1),('photo','post_page_378004348924081',NULL,'https://fbcdn-sphotos-b-a.akamaihd.net/hphotos-ak-ash2/v/t1.0-9/s130x130/550299_434036663320849_688950530_n.jpg?oh=cb2d8e11605df56a413e37f3e446df47&oe=54B8CAB3&__gda__=1420733153_89d914f5bbe78957161202679b0ce10f','https://www.facebook.com/365cps/photos/a.434036569987525.102069.378004348924081/434036663320849/?type=1&relevant_count=2','facebook.com','2012-10-31T03:48:13+0000',1351655293,1,1,0,0,0,0,0,1,'378004348924081_434036903320825','https://www.facebook.com/378004348924081/posts/434036903320825','365 Cancer Prevention Society',529,'2014-10-29 05:01:35',1),('photo','post_page_378004348924081','With love and patience_ nothing is impossible. Never underestimate the power of dreams and the influence of the human spirit.     NEVER GIVE UP!','https://fbcdn-sphotos-e-a.akamaihd.net/hphotos-ak-xpa1/v/t1.0-9/s130x130/3458_433647446693104_684149049_n.jpg?oh=73f2be904cfb7539eac2fabed8a1d8c4&oe=54B2227E&__gda__=1421897747_687fe52048c022e2bbb40310ddb697ab','https://www.facebook.com/365cps/photos/a.380809678643548.87582.378004348924081/433647446693104/?type=1&relevant_count=1','facebook.com','2012-10-30T09:16:15+0000',1351588575,1,1,0,0,0,0,0,1,'378004348924081_433647460026436','https://www.facebook.com/378004348924081/posts/433647460026436','365 Cancer Prevention Society',530,'2014-10-29 05:01:35',1),('photo','post_page_378004348924081','Sweet and Sour Chicken with Brown Rice    2 cups cooked brown rice  1 Tbsp. low-sodium soy sauce  1/3 cup rice vinegar  2 Tbsp. cornstarch  1/4 cup apricot preserves  2 Tbsp. olive oil_ divided  1 lb. boneless skinless chicken breasts_ cut into bite-size pieces  4 tsp. minced ginger  4 cloves minced garlic  1 cup reduced-sodium chicken broth  6 cups frozen vegetable mixture  1 can of sliced water chestnuts_ drained  Pinch crushed red pepper flakes (optional)  Salt and freshly ground pepper_ to taste    Prepare rice according to package directions. Set aside. Whisk soy sauce_ vinegar_ cornstarch and apricot preserves in a small mixing bowl and set aside as well.    Heat 1 Tbsp. oil in large skillet over medium to high heat. Add chicken to skillet and cook undisturbed for 2 minutes. Continue cooking_ stirring occasionally until starting to brown_ about 2 additional minutes. Transfer chicken to a plate.    Add remaining 1 Tbsp. oil_ ginger and garlic to the skillet and cook over medium-high heat_ about 30 seconds. Add chicken broth and bring to a boil_ stirring occasionally. Add frozen vegetables_ reduce heat_ cover and simmer under the vegetables are thawed_ about 5 minutes. Do not overcook vegetables.    Return cooked chicken to the pan. Add water chestnuts. Whisk the reserved sauce and add to the skillet. Add a pinch of red pepper flakes_ if desired. Simmer_ stir occasionally until the sauce thickens and chicken is heated through. Transfer chicken to a serving platter. Season with salt and pepper. Serve.','https://scontent-a.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xfp1/v/t1.0-9/s130x130/406855_433646923359823_1400982587_n.jpg?oh=f99d01f040f6e8e7e980cc321462ca83&oe=54F83E3B','https://www.facebook.com/365cps/photos/a.380809678643548.87582.378004348924081/433646923359823/?type=1&relevant_count=1','facebook.com','2012-10-30T09:13:47+0000',1351588427,2,3,0,0,0,0,0,2,'378004348924081_433646936693155','https://www.facebook.com/378004348924081/posts/433646936693155','365 Cancer Prevention Society',531,'2014-10-29 05:01:35',1),('photo','post_page_378004348924081','Broccoli with toufu!    Ingredients:      1 onion_ diced      4 cloves garlic_ minced      3 tbsp olive oil      approx 2 cups broccoli_ chopped      1 block firm or extra firm tofu_ pressed      1 1/2 tsp ginger powder      1/4 tsp cayenne pepper      3 tbsp corn starch      1/4 cup soy sauce      1 cup water    Preparation:  Cut tofu into 1 inch cubes.    in a large skillet_ sautee onions and garlic in olive oil until onions turn clear_ about 3-5 minutes.    Add the tofu_ ginger_ cayenne and broccoli to the pan and continue to cook until broccoli is done_ another 6-8 minutes.    In a separate small bowl_ mix together the corn starch_ soy sauce and water_ then add this mixture to the broccoli and tofu. Cook until sauce thickens_ then remove from heat.','https://scontent-b.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xfa1/v/t1.0-9/s130x130/531124_433645950026587_969841809_n.jpg?oh=2a47820cb25499e139fd2ccdb1c51710&oe=54F81F6D','https://www.facebook.com/365cps/photos/a.380809678643548.87582.378004348924081/433645950026587/?type=1&relevant_count=1','facebook.com','2012-10-30T09:09:53+0000',1351588193,2,2,0,0,0,0,0,2,'378004348924081_433645966693252','https://www.facebook.com/378004348924081/posts/433645966693252','365 Cancer Prevention Society',532,'2014-10-29 05:01:35',1),('status','post_page_378004348924081','Understanding Breast Cancer â†’ Symptoms of Breast Cancer Symptoms of Breast Cancer  Initially_ breast cancer may not cause any symptoms. A lump may be too small for you to feel or to cause any unusual changes you can notice on your own. Often_ an abnormal area turns up on a screening mammogram (x-ray of the breast)_ which leads to further testing.  In some cases_ however_ the first sign of breast cancer is a new lump or mass in the breast that you or your doctor can feel. A lump that is painless_ hard_ and has uneven edges is more likely to be cancer. But sometimes cancers can be tender_ soft_ and rounded. So it_s important to have anything unusual checked by your doctor.  According to the American Cancer Society_ any of the following unusual changes in the breast can be a symptom of breast cancer:      swelling of all or part of the breast     skin irritation or dimpling     breast pain     nipple pain or the nipple turning inward     redness_ scaliness_ or thickening of the nipple or breast skin     a nipple discharge other than breast milk     a lump in the underarm area  These changes also can be signs of less serious conditions that are not cancerous_ such as an infection or a cyst. Itâ€™s important to get any breast changes checked out promptly by a doctor',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2012-10-30T08:54:32+0000',1351587272,1,1,0,0,0,0,0,1,'378004348924081_433643283360187','https://www.facebook.com/378004348924081/posts/433643283360187','365 Cancer Prevention Society',533,'2014-10-29 05:01:35',1),('photo','post_page_378004348924081','Chocolate layered dessert For Cancer Patients!      Ingredients:  1 cup flour  7 tablespoons margarine or butter  1/2 cup chopped pecans  Directions     - Preheat oven to 350Â°F. Mix all ingredients and press into an ungreased 13x9x2-inch pan.   - Bake 20 minutes. Cool_ then top with cream cheese layer (recipe follows). Refrigerate until serving.    Cream cheese layer Ingredients:  3/4 cup frozen fat-free whipped topping  1 (8-ounce) package fat-free cream cheese  2/3 cup powdered sugar  Directions    Combine ingredients in mixer and beat only until well blended. Spread on top of first layer. Top with pudding layer (recipe follows).    Pudding layer Ingredients:  1 (4-serving) package instant vanilla pudding  1 (4-serving) package instant chocolate pudding  3 cups skim milk  1 teaspoon vanilla extract  1 1/4 cups frozen fat-free whipped topping_ thawed  Directions    - Mix pudding with milk_ beat according to directions on package.  - After thickened_ add vanilla. Spread on top of cream cheese layer. Cover dessert with whipped topping','https://fbcdn-sphotos-d-a.akamaihd.net/hphotos-ak-xfa1/v/t1.0-9/s130x130/28874_433032460087936_1389729051_n.jpg?oh=75a25340dd7a238cfc89b14bf90231bd&oe=54F21271&__gda__=1420783574_63b73ec6b5061237fc93d43f2bb2b010','https://www.facebook.com/365cps/photos/a.380809678643548.87582.378004348924081/433032460087936/?type=1&relevant_count=1','facebook.com',