a per week have an 87 percent higher chance of developing pancreatic cancer compared to individuals who do not consume soft drinks.     Excess sugar doesnâ€™t directly cause cancer but promotes proliferation of tumors by providing them a steady supply of nourishment. In the process_ these tumors might show signs of malignancy and finally cause cancers of the digestive system.    Extract from: nursebuff.com','https://fbcdn-sphotos-c-a.akamaihd.net/hphotos-ak-ash2/v/t1.0-9/s130x130/1044983_544131208978060_1166029484_n.jpg?oh=e94cdaa6564e66fb3bf94b6a0968e011&oe=54B02E28&__gda__=1421537193_1ea621266045281da380ecff1cacc271','https://www.facebook.com/365cps/photos/a.380809678643548.87582.378004348924081/544131208978060/?type=1&relevant_count=1','facebook.com','2013-07-05T05:49:40+0000',1373003380,2,2,0,0,0,0,0,2,'378004348924081_544131218978059','https://www.facebook.com/378004348924081/posts/544131218978059','365 Cancer Prevention Society',656,'2014-10-29 05:02:21',1),('photo','post_page_378004348924081','What are the cancer causing food?     4) Doughnuts     â€œReaderâ€™s Digestâ€ says it all: doughnuts are a disastrous foods to eat during break fast. And as it turned out_ it seems that this sugary treat can be disastrous any time of the day if taken in excess. This is because_ doughnuts contain high amounts of sugar_ deep-fried in hydrogenated oil and are made up of refined products (white flour)- â€“ -three necessary ingredients to create potent carcinogens.    Extract: nursebuff.com','https://fbcdn-sphotos-b-a.akamaihd.net/hphotos-ak-xfa1/v/t1.0-9/s130x130/1000155_542673455790502_16394752_n.jpg?oh=21770c86f9d945fee89636393e4e9d10&oe=54F2CAA5&__gda__=1420945154_cce418d320a0d47659f73a9fccaac097','https://www.facebook.com/365cps/photos/a.380809678643548.87582.378004348924081/542673455790502/?type=1&relevant_count=1','facebook.com','2013-07-02T09:37:17+0000',1372757837,1,1,0,0,0,0,0,1,'378004348924081_542673462457168','https://www.facebook.com/378004348924081/posts/542673462457168','365 Cancer Prevention Society',657,'2014-10-29 05:02:21',1),('photo','post_page_378004348924081','Detox Exercise starts again tomorow on every Tuesday and Thursday! SEE U :)','https://scontent-b.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-frc3/v/t1.0-9/s130x130/945734_516172468440601_587792976_n.jpg?oh=aa5b4115d57ab6d1aca5fbddda72ae62&oe=54B681DF','https://www.facebook.com/365cps/photos/a.380809678643548.87582.378004348924081/516172468440601/?type=1','facebook.com','2013-07-01T06:47:19+0000',1372661239,6,6,0,0,0,0,0,6,'378004348924081_541949309196250','https://www.facebook.com/378004348924081/posts/541949309196250','365 Cancer Prevention Society',658,'2014-10-29 05:02:21',1),('photo','post_page_378004348924081','What are the cancer causing food?   3) Fried Potatoes     Fried potatoes_ commonly known in fast food terminologies as simply â€œfrench friesâ€_ have been the focus of health-related criticisms for years.     This is not surprising because potatoes of this type are being cooked using hydrogenated oils and trans-fatsâ€“two contributing factors to fatal heart diseases.     Moreover_ potatoes contain carbohydrates that release carcinogenic by-products called acrylamides during the deep-frying process. A Swedish study backed up this claim by revealing how acrylamides have helped in forming cancer cells among rats.    Extract: nursebuff.com','https://scontent-a.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xap1/v/t1.0-9/p130x130/936459_541906095867238_1693150866_n.jpg?oh=5dd9b7f75edc4c7d95961928d20426da&oe=54C21FFF','https://www.facebook.com/365cps/photos/a.380809678643548.87582.378004348924081/541906095867238/?type=1&relevant_count=1','facebook.com','2013-07-01T03:50:45+0000',1372650645,3,3,0,0,0,0,0,3,'378004348924081_541906109200570','https://www.facebook.com/378004348924081/posts/541906109200570','365 Cancer Prevention Society',659,'2014-10-29 05:02:21',1),('photo','post_page_378004348924081','What are the cancer causing food?  2) Hot dogs (those that are high in nitrites)    Kids love to have hot dogs in the table but if you donâ€™t choose the right product_ you might just increase your familyâ€™s chance of getting cancer.     According to Cancer Prevention Coalition_ eating hot dogs that have high amounts of sodium nitrites can increase oneâ€™s chance of getting cancer. A research study that was conducted between 1980 to 1987 at Los Angeles      County has revealed that children who eat more than 12 hot dogs a month are more likely to get leukemia_ a known cancer of the blood. Sodium nitrites  are known preservatives being used to combat botulism among processed meats but this same chemical can bind to amines upon cooking to form potent carcinogens that are also linked to cancers of the digestive system.    Extract: nursebuff.com','https://scontent-a.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-frc3/v/t1.0-9/s130x130/946833_540046236053224_243590847_n.jpg?oh=95245aab55e98784bf6da82a6ae566e7&oe=54AE03DB','https://www.facebook.com/365cps/photos/a.380809678643548.87582.378004348924081/540046236053224/?type=1&relevant_count=1','facebook.com','2013-06-27T08:41:33+0000',1372322493,6,6,1,1,0,2,0,9,'378004348924081_540046249386556','https://www.facebook.com/378004348924081/posts/540046249386556','365 Cancer Prevention Society',660,'2014-10-29 05:02:21',1),('photo','post_page_378004348924081','What are the cancer causing food?  1) Charred/Burnt meat    Eating charred or burnt meat is not actually delectable_ let alone free from any health hazards. According to National Cancer Institute_ eating burnt meat has been linked to cancers of the digestive system such as colon and stomach. In addition to this_ a research study led by Kristin Anderson of the University of Minnesota has claimed that eating charred meat can increase a personâ€™s chance of getting pancreatic cancer by almost 60%.    extract from www.nursebuff.com','https://fbcdn-sphotos-c-a.akamaihd.net/hphotos-ak-xap1/v/t1.0-9/s130x130/983977_539659746091873_1061076677_n.jpg?oh=863ac8a23f113cf2bb48604ac1f91eb4&oe=54F7327E&__gda__=1425369475_a3c66d0d0199131cf4ac69f03d53d990','https://www.facebook.com/365cps/photos/a.380809678643548.87582.378004348924081/539659746091873/?type=1&relevant_count=1','facebook.com','2013-06-26T10:05:34+0000',1372241134,5,5,0,0,0,0,0,5,'378004348924081_539659756091872','https://www.facebook.com/378004348924081/posts/539659756091872','365 Cancer Prevention Society',661,'2014-10-29 05:02:21',1),('status','post_page_378004348924081','â€œPain is temporary. Quitting lasts forever.â€  â€• Lance Armstrong_ Every Second Counts  Are you fighting a hard battle? Dont give up!',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2013-06-24T03:18:06+0000',1372043886,1,1,0,0,0,0,0,1,'378004348924081_538548332869681','https://www.facebook.com/378004348924081/posts/538548332869681','365 Cancer Prevention Society',662,'2014-10-29 05:02:21',1),('photo','post_page_378004348924081','365CPS FLAG DAY IS OPEN FOR REGISTRATION NOW!  *BE A VOICE ON THE STREETS TO PREVENT & FIGHT CANCER*   GET YOUR BUDDIES TOGETHER TO BE FLAGGERS ON 07 Dec 2013 (SATURDAY).....  For new sign ups_ please follow the link below to register!   https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1B74MOrSlUlkwkKHa2SIIduoagKdZO4PxRnKZwigGZWk/viewform','https://scontent-a.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xaf1/v/t1.0-9/s130x130/1011397_537287496329098_1264012301_n.jpg?oh=b0869daaa23e6e89101afbbfabd48a47&oe=54F3A695','https://www.facebook.com/365cps/photos/a.380809678643548.87582.378004348924081/537287496329098/?type=1&relevant_count=1','facebook.com','2013-06-21T04:21:37+0000',1371788497,1,1,0,0,0,204,0,205,'378004348924081_537287502995764','https://www.facebook.com/378004348924081/posts/537287502995764','365 Cancer Prevention Society',663,'2014-10-29 05:02:21',1),('photo','post_page_378004348924081','365 Cancer Prevention Society added a new photo.','https://fbcdn-sphotos-b-a.akamaihd.net/hphotos-ak-frc3/v/t1.0-9/s130x130/944139_537269139664267_1513520646_n.jpg?oh=b7db0cb0414a9bfb4a3a125c0fcee8d8&oe=54F8DD9F&__gda__=1421573364_3791707263b6f57d87059be5d6a55b21','https://www.facebook.com/365cps/photos/a.380809678643548.87582.378004348924081/537269139664267/?type=1&relevant_count=1','facebook.com','2013-06-21T03:31:17+0000',1371785477,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'378004348924081_537269149664266','https://www.facebook.com/378004348924081/posts/537269149664266','365 Cancer Prevention Society',664,'2014-10-29 05:02:21',1),('photo','post_page_378004348924081','MAKE A GARDEN POTATO SALAD!     Ingredients   3 lbs potatoes (6 large)   1 cup chopped celery   1/2 cup sliced green onion   2 tablespoons chopped parsley     DRESSING   1 cup low-fat cottage cheese   3/4 cup skim milk   3 tablespoons lemon juice   2 tablespoons cider vinegar   1/2 teaspoon celery seed   1/2 teaspoon dillweed   1/2 teaspoon dry mustard   1/2 teaspoon white pepper     Preparation   In a blender_ blend cottage cheese_ milk_ lemon juice_ vinegar_ celery seed_ dillweed_ dry mustard_ and white pepper until smooth. Chill for 1 hour.     Scrub potatoes; boil in jackets until tender. Cool; peel. Cut into 1/2-inch cubes. Add celery_ green onion_ and parsley.   Pour chilled cottage cheese mixture over vegetables; mix well. Chill at least 30 minutes before serving     source: www.cancer.gov_ accessed 21 Jun 13','https://scontent-b.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xfa1/v/t1.0-9/s130x130/1001777_537252416332606_491069850_n.jpg?oh=1265138e6d7cbcc9e3c2da3fe57b7c44&oe=54B38D18','https://www.facebook.com/365cps/photos/a.380809678643548.87582.378004348924081/537252416332606/?type=1&relevant_count=1','facebook.com','2013-06-21T02:45:31+0000',1371782731,2,2,0,0,0,0,0,2,'378004348924081_537252422999272','https://www.facebook.com/378004348924081/posts/537252422999272','365 Cancer Prevention Society',665,'2014-10-29 05:02:21',1),('status','post_page_378004348924081','Due to the presence Haze problem_ we will stop the 1_3_5 morning exercise with immediate effect till 2 July_(Tues). From July onward we will have the detox exercise every Tues n Thursday_7am-7.45am. No more spiritual detox devotion n breakfast. If the PSI is