'post_page_378004348924081','Prevent Cancer by Eating Your Veggies!    There are so many good reasons to eat more vegetables â€“ heart health_ brain health_ weight management_ and cancer prevention are each aided and maintained by eating the right vegetables. When it comes to healthy foods like fruits and vegetables_ a bonus is this: When we fill up on things that are good for us_ weâ€™ll automatically eat less of the ones that are bad for us','https://fbcdn-sphotos-h-a.akamaihd.net/hphotos-ak-xfa1/v/t1.0-9/s130x130/581125_486930424698139_1430682040_n.jpg?oh=9a8aded6847c31b6eaafde2f10a65a05&oe=54BB5FDF&__gda__=1425031786_39b9528360107278d4f4930d0a17f429','https://www.facebook.com/365cps/photos/a.380809678643548.87582.378004348924081/486930424698139/?type=1&relevant_count=1','facebook.com','2013-02-21T01:45:58+0000',1361411158,7,7,0,0,0,0,0,7,'378004348924081_486930438031471','https://www.facebook.com/378004348924081/posts/486930438031471','365 Cancer Prevention Society',735,'2014-10-29 05:02:21',1),('photo','post_page_378004348924081','Prevent Cancer with Garlic!    I canâ€™t imagine anyone not liking the taste of garlic â€“ maybe not straight out of the bulb_ of course_ but garlic truly is a beautiful ingredient.  Keep garlic bulbs (or at least jars of chopped garlic in olive oil) on hand at all times.  Theyâ€™re excellent chopped and added to stew_ soups_ hamburgers_ pasta salad_ spaghetti sauce_ chiliâ€¦. Garlic contains a great number of compounds that can protect against cancer.  These compounds appear to increase the activity of immune cells that fight cancer and indirectly help break down cancer causing substances. Garlic seems to be particularly useful against skin cancer_ colon cancer_ and lung cancer.','https://scontent-b.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xpa1/v/t1.0-9/s130x130/11020_486930031364845_1126144636_n.jpg?oh=e50d52bb3d586cb8cfebc9d1e826a129&oe=54F1D4AE','https://www.facebook.com/365cps/photos/a.380809678643548.87582.378004348924081/486930031364845/?type=1&relevant_count=1','facebook.com','2013-02-21T01:44:09+0000',1361411049,6,6,0,0,0,0,0,6,'378004348924081_486930051364843','https://www.facebook.com/378004348924081/posts/486930051364843','365 Cancer Prevention Society',736,'2014-10-29 05:02:21',1),('photo','post_page_378004348924081','Come join us in our Art & Craft Class on 13-15 March 2013 (Wed-Fri)     Do call us to register now! Limited seats only (:   +65 6337 3368','https://scontent-a.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-ash2/v/t1.0-9/s130x130/560516_486048771452971_982081043_n.jpg?oh=71baeb4be9dcdb2de57b5eb2aa4c3620&oe=54AA386B','https://www.facebook.com/365cps/photos/a.380809678643548.87582.378004348924081/486048771452971/?type=1&relevant_count=1','facebook.com','2013-02-19T09:05:32+0000',1361264732,4,4,0,0,0,0,0,4,'378004348924081_486048784786303','https://www.facebook.com/378004348924081/posts/486048784786303','365 Cancer Prevention Society',737,'2014-10-29 05:02:21',1),('photo','post_page_378004348924081','VOLUNTEER YOURSELF FOR A CANCER CAUSE! :)    CLICK BELOW TO JOIN US NOW!  To fill it out_ please visit:   https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1XaGUtBLHF9My8VsSjhVHtalcQtRQvu0kb4CxzW4L9RY/viewform?sid=625757664a1475fa&token=i0rV4DwBAAA.h_HLKrpTLSBsxlooOfz6Cg.h9iiJ9JL90r9nQYXfViU2g','https://scontent-b.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-ash2/v/t1.0-9/s130x130/560379_484514238273091_1265940526_n.jpg?oh=226b4cd363e9538eaaefe924c24d150f&oe=54ED87BF','https://www.facebook.com/365cps/photos/a.380809678643548.87582.378004348924081/484514238273091/?type=1&relevant_count=1','facebook.com','2013-02-16T05:02:14+0000',1360990934,1,1,0,0,0,0,0,1,'378004348924081_484514248273090','https://www.facebook.com/378004348924081/posts/484514248273090','365 Cancer Prevention Society',738,'2014-10-29 05:02:21',1),('photo','post_page_378004348924081','Happiness lies for those who cry_ those who have searched_ and those who have tried_ for only they can appreciate the importance of people who have touched their lives.','https://fbcdn-sphotos-e-a.akamaihd.net/hphotos-ak-xap1/v/t1.0-9/s130x130/68928_483191211738727_699429100_n.jpg?oh=e91151b3123aa573f2fbd70c7c2be564&oe=54C2253B&__gda__=1420564323_49a6ed531e2c004d3ab51cb8dc3aaded','https://www.facebook.com/365cps/photos/a.380809678643548.87582.378004348924081/483191211738727/?type=1&relevant_count=1','facebook.com','2013-02-14T02:58:41+0000',1360810721,1,1,0,0,0,0,0,1,'378004348924081_483191225072059','https://www.facebook.com/378004348924081/posts/483191225072059','365 Cancer Prevention Society',739,'2014-10-29 05:02:21',1),('photo','post_page_378004348924081','Healthy_ quick tea time snack â€“ Pearl Corn    Pearl Corn is different from the normal corn because it is so sweet_ have bigger kernels and can be eaten fresh. It is call pearl corn because of the white kernels. Nowadays_ most wet markets sell fresh pearl corn which comes from Cameron Highlands. It is more expensive than regular corn but it is worth the money.    Steam it over a pot of boiling water and slather either salt and butter on the three cobs. You can also pop the corn into the microwave and put it on high for about 2-3 minutes to cook it.     Of course_ you need to peel off the outer layers which are the leaves and the corn silk or the hairy stuffs and then_ wash the cobs clean before steaming. It is good to give to have steamed corn instead of fresh ones because we never know what bacteria sticks to them. Steaming will be safer (:','https://scontent-b.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xfa1/v/t1.0-9/s130x130/69604_483189055072276_1027220635_n.jpg?oh=7aa02f28509491bf34929ad000673464&oe=54C30F89','https://www.facebook.com/365cps/photos/a.380809678643548.87582.378004348924081/483189055072276/?type=1&relevant_count=1','facebook.com','2013-02-14T02:50:24+0000',1360810224,2,2,0,0,0,0,0,2,'378004348924081_483189061738942','https://www.facebook.com/378004348924081/posts/483189061738942','365 Cancer Prevention Society',740,'2014-10-29 05:02:21',1),('photo','post_page_378004348924081','Just grab a packet of frozen green peas and a packet of mint leaves from the supermarket shelf && you can start cooking your green pea and mint soup!     Recipe for green pea and mint soup    -2 cups stock  - 1 cup green peas (if you are using frozen ones_ you need to cook first_ if you are using canned ones_ you can just dump into the food processor)  - 1 handful of mint leaves  - A bit of chopped garlic and onion  - 1 tiny cube of butter  - 1/2 cup of cream or milk  - Salt/pepper to taste    _________________________________________    Heat butter and sweat the onion and garlic. Add in green peas and stir till you are sure it is cooked. You donâ€™t want the â€˜green smellâ€™ of uncooked peas_ you know? However_ donâ€™t over cook it or it will turn an ugly yellow. Just taste the peas and you can tell if it is cooked.    Dump everything_ including the cream and fresh mint leaves into the food processor and blend till smooth. If you like your fibres_ then fine. But I hate the thought of the pea husk (or skin) fermenting in my belly_ giving me major flatulence fart fest (3Fs!) so I strained the liquid.    Before serving_ heat through over low fire_ taking care not to boil it. Season with salt and pepper. Adjust the soup as the peas may cause the green goo to form into an ugly mess. Add some water or milk to make it â€˜slurpableâ€™ and not looking like blobs of green stuffs.','https://fbcdn-sphotos-g-a.akamaihd.net/hphotos-ak-xpa1/v/t1.0-9/s130x130/535902_483181345073047_1877931340_n.jpg?oh=721a4dc5a1876d74a63d0f83485700d2&oe=54C344F0&__gda__=1421825394_e5d63e6516d1706876db42db5fb64291','https://www.facebook.com/365cps/photos/a.380809678643548.87582.378004348924081/483181345073047/?type=1&relevant_count=1','facebook.com','2013-02-14T02:23:58+0000',1360808638,3,3,0,0,0,0,0,3,'378004348924081_483181361739712','https://www.facebook.com/378004348924081/posts/483181361739712','365 Cancer Prevention Society',741,'2014-10-29 05:02:21',1),('photo','post_page_378004348924081',NULL,'https://fbcdn-sphotos-a-a.akamaihd.net/hpho